    "id": 3473982765,
    "title": "Python website",
    "body": "# Extend Mosaic Documentation with Python Support\r\n\r\nThis PR extends the Mosaic documentation so Python users can follow the same examples and references as the YAML/JSON/JS tabs, and adds a short guide for using vgplot-style specs from Python.\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\n### Examples\r\nMost example pages now include a **Python tab** that inlines `docs/public/specs/python/<name>.py`, alongside JavaScript, YAML, and JSON. A few examples keep the Python (or JSON) tab commented out where the generated snippet is missing or invalid (e.g. `region-tests` JSON, `density-groups` / `facet-interval` / `protein-design` / `window-frame` Python).\r\n\r\n### Mosaic vgplot (Python)\r\nNew guide at `docs/vgplot-python/` describing:\r\n- `mosaic.vgplot`\r\n- `snake_case` helpers\r\n- `MosaicWidget` + declarative specs\r\n- Pointers to the shared spec format and vgplot API reference (including `camelCase` vs `snake_case`)\r\n\r\n### Navigation\r\nGuide dropdown and sidebar include **Mosaic vgplot Python** linking to `/vgplot-python/`.\r\n\r\n### API: Plot\r\n`docs/api/vgplot/plot.md` uses a code group with **JavaScript and Python examples** (mirrored structure and inline comments for attribute / mark / interactor / legend).\r\n\r\n### Python Spec Snippets\r\nAdds `docs/public/specs/python/*.py` files in the `Plot` / `DataSource` / `PlotMark` style used for the example tabs (aligned with the declarative spec where applicable).",
    "created_at": "2026-03-31T20:58:19Z",
